review_blob: Rating 18- Let me begin by saying I believe this beer is way overpriced in my area of the United States.  It costs between 10 and 12 dollars for a 6 pack which i think is way too high for a beer that to me tastes exactly like Budweiser.  The only aspect of this beer I actually like is the bottle itself and the simplicity of the label.  Other than that its a mediocre lager at best.  The commercials are funny though.

Rating 17- I bought a six pack of this beer one day because I was curious about it for a while.  It was about $5.50 for the sixer and I got home on a nice sunny day and drank a few outside.  Not that bad of a beer, and it is many times better than Corona for me.  Ive only had it in a bottle which Im sure makes a big difference as opposed to the can.

Rating 16- I have given this beer many chances throughout my drinking life and each time I try it I am reminded of why I dont ever buy it.  People swear by this beer and I honestly dont know how it has such a following.  It always tastes skunky to me and a warm sip of this is about the most disgusting thing you can put in your mouth.  If you add lime there is a chance you can finish the whole thing but I would never want to waste 30 dollars on a case, which is how much it costs in my area of the United States.

Rating 15- I really liked the aroma and look of this beer but I was surprised by how light it seemed.  I was a bit disappointed by the beer and I didnt think the apricot flavor came through as much as I wanted it to.  This is not a bad beer by any means but it just didnt knock my socks off.

Rating 14- This brew brings back memories for me of drinking with my uncles when i was still in high school, so it has a place for me.  I actually like the taste of it to a certain extent but can only handle so many of them before I either fill up from the excessive carbonation or just get sick of the taste of it.  This beer has its place, but its definitely not something everyone would enjoy.

Rating 13- This is just a horrible beer overall as far as Im concerned.  I could barely stomach just one can.  It is a cheap beer but honestly if you are going for beers just to get drunk on I would steer clear from this and get something like Coors Original or Piels if you can find it.  Not much to say about the taste of this beer other than it is highly carbonated with a harsh flavor that I really couldnt stand.

Rating 12- Actually not a terrible ultra light beer.  I would rather have Mich Ultra over Aspen Edge or MGD 64 anyday.  It also works nicely if u really want a beer after a workout but you dont want a heavy beer that is high in carbs.  There are definitely worse ultra light beers out there.
Rating 11- I hate original Rolling Rock and this beer is even more disgusting to me.  It really tastes like almost nothing except watery, carbonated, spoiled apple juice.

Rating 10- Affectionately called "Beast Light" by my crew, I actually like this beer more than regular Milwaukees Best.  If you have to drink this or cant afford anything else, try to get it in a bottle instead of a can, it makes a huge difference.

Rating 9 - Basically the only reason I gave this beer a 2 on the rating scale is because it is such a prevalent and classic beer of many of my friends who live in my small town.  We just refer to it as Beast for short and although I have basically always hated its taste I will drink it if Im at a party and there is nothing else to pour down my gullet.  Basically only good for getting wasted on.  This beer always reminds me of good times and spoiled wheat when i taste it.

I actually got a shirt as a gift from my friend in high school that has this beer logo on the front of it.  He bought it for me as a joke and its fitting because this beer is basically a joke.  It tastes worse than any other inexpensive bum beer I can think of except for maybe Wild Stallion.  Avoid it at all costs and if you do buy a beer like this I would say go for a Mickeys instead.  Unless of course you want to embrace your inner bum.

Honestly this beer is a must have for anyone who is a fan of hoppiness in their beer.  It tastes great and goes down smooth.  I shared it with a friend along with a great steak and a gorgeous, relaxing day outside.  It is a masterfully crafted ale and yet another amazing beer from Bells.

This offering from Bells is absolutely one of the best, if not the best stout I have ever had.  You can easily taste roasted malt and a great, sweet vanilla flavor throughout the whole beer.  In my opinion my friend and fellow beer taster hit the nail on the head when he described this beer as "beer candy."  This brew definitely deserves all the praise it receives and it wasnt even all that expensive either!  I will surely come back to this stout as many times as i can.

I was enthusiastic to try this beer when I brought it home from the store mainly because I was so curious about its taste.  I agree with some of the other raters in that it might be a good idea to share it with someone else because it is so thick and strong.  It comes on like a barley wine mixed with a heavy stout and almost has the consistency of watery molasses.  It is an enjoyable beer however, but one bottle or even half of one is about enough.  All in all my friends and I were glad we gave it a shot.  However it may take you off guard as it did myself if you are not prepared for its intense taste.

This is definitely one of the best IPAs i have ever had the pleasure of drinking.  The deScription on the bottle states that it is similar to the regular Stone IPA but with an undeniable Belgian influence because of the yeast strain they used to brew the beer.  I was skeptical at first and believed I would be drinking a glorified Stone IPA, however I was pleasantly mistaken.  This beer definitely takes on an identity all its own.  One can honestly taste the distinct flavor produced by the Belgian yeast in the brew and it only adds to the greatness of the overall flavor of the beer.  The hoppiness is excellent and exactly what one would expect from a great IPA.  The aroma smells of a refreshing citrus enhanced by the scent of the yeast.  It is quite a refreshing brew and would be great to drink on a warm or hot day just relaxing outside.

This stout was recommended by the owner of my local beer store and I decided to give it a try.  I really liked the roasted and smoky taste of the malts in the beer.  It has the intensely black color that one would expect from a Russian Stout style beer and the head is a nice tan color.  If you like the taste of coffee in your beer then this will be a great stout for you, since the java taste comes through quite intensely.  It also has a bit of a sour taste to it, but nothing overbearing and hard to swallow.  All around a nice stout beer.
beer_name: The Duck-Rabbit Rabid Duck Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: This is the first Vertical Epic that I have had the pleasure of tasting and I will say that from the first sip i knew this would be one of my favorite beers.  I purchased this beer on a whim one day at my local beer store and could not believe how thick and complex, yet smooth and crisp it was.  You are instantly able to taste all different kinds of spice notes in the beer and the pour is a beautiful dark body with an off-white head that sits like a crown at the top of your glass.  Although it may resemble a heavy stout in appearance, the Vertical Epic 09 is much lighter than it seems yet this does not take away at all from the flavor of the beer.  This beer has brought me into the cult of the Vertical Epic and I cant wait for the next one to come out from Stone.

I had this beer in a bottle that had been on the shelf in the beer store for at least 7 months.  I put off trying it because it was pricey and there were so many other glorious stones to try.  I eventually bought it because it was almost out of stock at the store, and Im so glad i did.  It is excellent and deserves the praise it has received.  The color and thickness of the pour let you know how intense your drinking experience will be before you even take a sip of the beer.  I made sure to take a good whiff and savor the hoppy ale aroma before I began to indulge in the brew.  Finally upon sipping both my friend and I agreed that it was truly an excellent beer and yet another offering from Stone that did not disappoint.  If you love the original Arrogant Bastard you will definitely adore this beer.
